'''Decuriae''' was a [[Ancient Roman units of measurement|Roman]] unit of measurement applied to [[civitas]] of native peoples.{{refn|group="Note"|Decuriae was a Roman term used by Elder Pliny in his Natural History completed in 70 AD based on official registers. Each civitas had a number of decuriae assigned to it as an indication of its size. A Roman division of native peoples. <ref>Wilkes, J. J. The Illyrians, 1992, {{ISBN|0-631-19807-5}}, page 215)</ref>}} It had been mentioned by [[Pliny the Elder]] at 70&nbsp;AD in his work, [[Natural History (Pliny)|''Natural History'']].
